    <item>
      <title>Personal</title>
      <link>https://unpilbaek.github.io/personal/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 22 Apr 2021 13:05:37 -0700</pubDate>
      <guid>https://unpilbaek.github.io/personal/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;CAVEAT.&lt;/em&gt; This is a draft post. The contents shown here shall be developed fully
soon.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;bbooksb&#34;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Books&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I regularly update my reading status at
&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/99643130-unpil-baek&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Goodreads&lt;/a&gt;.
&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.goodreads.com/user/99643130/favorite_authors&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Here&lt;/a&gt; is the list of
my favorite authors. If you ask me the books that influenced me the most so far,
they would be The Bible, Plato&amp;rsquo;s &lt;em&gt;Republic&lt;/em&gt;, Augustine&amp;rsquo;s &lt;em&gt;Confessions&lt;/em&gt;, and
Frankl&amp;rsquo;s &lt;em&gt;Man&amp;rsquo;s Search for Meaning&lt;/em&gt;.  I also write
&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/99643130-unpil-baek?order=d&amp;amp;sort=review&amp;amp;view=reviews&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;reviews&lt;/a&gt;
from time to time. Feel free to follow me!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;bfilmsb&#34;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Films&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I regularly update films I&amp;rsquo;ve watched at
&lt;a href=&#34;https://letterboxd.com/unpilbaek/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Letterboxd&lt;/a&gt;. Feel free to follow me!  If you
ask me my top three favorite directors, they would be Stanley Kubrick, Ingmar
Bergman, and Akira Kurosawa. For great TV miniseries, I recommend &amp;ldquo;Fanny and
Alexander&amp;rdquo; (Bergman, 1983) and &amp;ldquo;Dekalog&amp;rdquo; (Kieślowski, 1988). (&amp;ldquo;Berlin
Alexanderplatz&amp;rdquo; (Fassbinder, 1980) is on my to-watch list.)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;bquotesb&#34;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Quotes&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;ldquo;Zorba,&amp;rdquo; I shouted, &amp;ldquo;come, teach me to dance!&amp;rdquo; Zorba leaped to his feet, his
face glowing. &amp;ldquo;Dance, Boss?&amp;rdquo; he asked. &amp;ldquo;Dance? Come!&amp;rdquo; (&lt;em&gt;Zorba the Greek&lt;/em&gt;, Nikos
Kazantzakis; tr. Peter Bien) A memorable associated &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2AzpHvLWFUM&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;video
clip&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;There is a time for everything, and a season for every activity under heavens:
&amp;hellip;  (Ecclesiastes 3:1-8, NIV). Full verse reference
&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Ecclesiastes%203&amp;amp;version=NIV&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.
There is a
